                   or bearer
            </rs>, and which said false, forged, and counterfeited order for the payment of money is in the words and figures following, that is to say,</p>

               <p>"Carey-street, September 15th, 1785, Sir 
               <persName id="t17860111-62-person915">
                  James
                   Esdaile
               <interp inst="t17860111-62-person915" type="surname" value="Esdaile"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17860111-62-person915" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17860111-62-person915" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             and Co. pay 
               <persName id="t17860111-62-person916">
                  Thomas
                   Maddocks
               <interp inst="t17860111-62-person916" type="surname" value="Maddocks"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17860111-62-person916" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17860111-62-person916" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , Esq. or bearer, the sum of thirty pounds sterling. 30. 
               <persName id="t17860111-62-person917">
                  John
                   Griffin
               <interp inst="t17860111-62-person917" type="surname" value="Griffin"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17860111-62-person917" type="given" value="John"></interp>
